00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:37.166
[bus rumbling]

512
00:32:37.250 --> 00:32:43.291
[suspenseful music playing]

513
00:32:43.375 --> 00:32:47.666
[bus quietly creaking]

514
00:32:53.916 --> 00:32:55.916
[bus creaks]

515
00:32:56.000 --> 00:33:01.250
[suspenseful music continues]

516
00:33:05.666 --> 00:33:07.208
[suspenseful music crescendos]

517
00:33:09.916 --> 00:33:11.000
I got you. buddy.

518
00:33:20.916 --> 00:33:22.958
So. uh. what are we going to do with her?

519
00:33:24.916 --> 00:33:26.791
[police siren blaring]

520
00:33:28.208 --> 00:33:29.375
Not our problem now.

521
00:33:29.458 --> 00:33:30.833
[vehicle approaching]

522
00:33:34.625 --> 00:33:35.708
Better late than never.

523
00:33:39.666 --> 00:33:40.666
[Spike] Hey.

524
00:33:48.541 --> 00:33:51.125
Captain Shankar. Provincial Police.

525
00:33:54.250 --> 00:33:55.291
What happened here?

526
00:33:56.125 --> 00:33:57.416
Attempted kidnapping.

527
00:34:04.958 --> 00:34:06.041
Her gun.

528
00:34:11.250 --> 00:34:12.416
[Shankar speaking Nepali]

529
00:34:14.625 --> 00:34:19.958
[indistinct chatter]

530
00:34:20.791 --> 00:34:25.916
[eerie music playing]

531
00:34:28.666 --> 00:34:31.458
[tense music plays]

532
00:34:34.666 --> 00:34:35.958
Ah. shit.

533
00:34:37.000 --> 00:34:38.291
Nasty.

534
00:34:38.375 --> 00:34:40.916
Well. she ain't making it up to Everest.

535
00:34:41.291 --> 00:34:42.916
Not today at least. But...

536
00:34:43.958 --> 00:34:48.083
I reckon a spot weld might get her down
to the Araniko Highway.

537
00:34:49.125 --> 00:34:52.041
I'm a fair hand with a welding torch.
if you've got one.

538
00:34:52.541 --> 00:34:53.541
Are ya?

539
00:34:53.875 --> 00:34:54.916
Bloody oath I do.

540
00:34:55.833 --> 00:34:57.166
You're a bloody beauty. mate.

541
00:34:58.041 --> 00:35:00.583
[Spike groans] I'll bring her around.

542
00:35:02.333 --> 00:35:03.250
Be still.

543
00:35:03.333 --> 00:35:07.125
- [dogs barking]
- [footsteps receding]

544
00:35:07.208 --> 00:35:08.208
You fight well.

545
00:35:10.000 --> 00:35:12.291
You're not bad yourself. for a Buddhist.

546
00:35:13.625 --> 00:35:15.625
Shows how much you know about Buddhists.

547
00:35:18.041 --> 00:35:20.541
You'll have to show me
that roundhouse kick.

548
00:35:21.958 --> 00:35:23.250
You're too old.

549
00:35:23.333 --> 00:35:24.500
I have young prana.

550
00:35:25.250 --> 00:35:26.250
Prana?

551
00:35:27.291 --> 00:35:28.416
Prana is Hindu.

552
00:35:29.708 --> 00:35:31.291
Life force. right?

553
00:35:38.041 --> 00:35:39.250
[goat bleats]

554
00:35:40.333 --> 00:35:42.416
[footsteps approaching]

555
00:35:42.500 --> 00:35:43.500
Young man.

556
00:35:43.833 --> 00:35:45.333
- Officer.
- [officer speaking Nepali]

557
00:35:45.750 --> 00:35:47.708
I need some information.

558
00:35:47.791 --> 00:35:48.791
[speaking Nepali]

559
00:35:50.250 --> 00:35:52.500
- Uh.
- [Dhani] He doesn't speak English.

560
00:35:54.541 --> 00:35:56.250
I need to know the status of the young man

561
00:35:56.333 --> 00:35:58.458
you and Mr. McCann
saved from the kidnappers.

562
00:35:58.875 --> 00:35:59.875
[speaking Nepali]

563
00:36:00.625 --> 00:36:01.750
[speaking Nepali]

564
00:36:01.833 --> 00:36:03.583
[speaking Nepali]

565
00:36:05.041 --> 00:36:07.750
- He's awake. No need to worry.
- I'd like to know his name.

566
00:36:08.958 --> 00:36:09.958
Hey!

567
00:36:12.166 --> 00:36:13.416
[speaking Nepali]

568
00:36:13.958 --> 00:36:14.833
Vijay Rai.

569
00:36:14.916 --> 00:36:17.875
[foreboding music plays]

570
00:36:17.958 --> 00:36:19.500
Did he just say Vijay Rai?

571
00:36:22.875 --> 00:36:24.333
We wouldn't be in Kodari. would we?

572
00:36:26.000 --> 00:36:27.000
Yes.

573
00:36:28.250 --> 00:36:29.250
This is Kodari.

574
00:36:30.416 --> 00:36:31.916
We've not had the pleasure.

575
00:36:32.541 --> 00:36:35.250
- I'm Dhani Yangchen.
- I'm sorry. Evan Myers.

576
00:36:36.541 --> 00:36:38.833
I saw you speak in Pokhara
last year. Professor.

577
00:36:39.291 --> 00:36:41.125
- It is my honor.
- Oh. thank you.

578
00:36:41.791 --> 00:36:43.267
- [Starr] Dad!
- [footsteps approaching]

579
00:36:43.291 --> 00:36:45.208
Dad. you've got to see these rugs.

580
00:36:46.166 --> 00:36:49.125
I believe you met my daughter.
Starr. this is Dhani Yangchen.

581
00:36:49.791 --> 00:36:50.791
Hi.

582
00:36:51.500 --> 00:36:52.500
Hi.

583
00:36:53.458 --> 00:36:54.791
You have good taste.

584
00:36:54.875 --> 00:36:57.416
Kodari rugs are loved all over the world.

585
00:36:59.625 --> 00:37:00.833
Where are all the people?

586
00:37:03.250 --> 00:37:04.250
Gone.

587
00:37:04.875 --> 00:37:06.166
There has been trouble here.

588
00:37:07.166 --> 00:37:08.166
[Myers] Hmm.

589
00:37:08.500 --> 00:37:09.541
What kind of trouble?

590
00:37:10.375 --> 00:37:11.375
Dad?

591
00:37:12.208 --> 00:37:13.250
It's a land dispute.

592
00:37:13.791 --> 00:37:17.041
A man named Rudra Yash wants to build
the largest dam in the Himalayas.

593
00:37:17.125 --> 00:37:20.291
- One of the families won't sell.
- Land is all these people have.

594
00:37:21.333 --> 00:37:22.333
[Myers] Indeed.

595
00:37:23.958 --> 00:37:26.083
- Excuse me. Dhani. You okay here?
- Yeah.

596
00:37:30.375 --> 00:37:32.708
Um. what you did on that bus. That was...

597
00:37:34.500 --> 00:37:35.541
it was unbelievable.

598
00:37:37.166 --> 00:37:38.166
[chuckles]

599
00:37:38.500 --> 00:37:39.500
You helped.

600
00:37:40.708 --> 00:37:41.708
Call me Dhani.

601
00:37:43.583 --> 00:37:44.934
Can you teach me to fight like that?

602
00:37:44.958 --> 00:37:48.041
[pots banging distantly]

603
00:37:48.125 --> 00:37:49.583
If you promise to remember...

604
00:37:50.541 --> 00:37:53.625
it's not about the teacher.
always the student.

605
00:37:55.958 --> 00:37:56.958
Yes.

606
00:37:57.541 --> 00:38:00.333
[chuckles]

607
00:38:04.791 --> 00:38:08.958
- [car engines revving]
- [dramatic music playing]

608
00:38:09.041 --> 00:38:10.583
[hissing]

609
00:38:12.958 --> 00:38:16.375
[engines revving]

610
00:38:16.458 --> 00:38:22.791
[dramatic music continues]

611
00:38:38.083 --> 00:38:41.083
[sinister music plays]

612
00:38:41.166 --> 00:38:42.166
[car door closes]

613
00:38:48.000 --> 00:38:49.000
[engine revving]

614
00:38:49.041 --> 00:38:50.541
[bus horn honking]

615
00:38:51.291 --> 00:38:56.291
[man 6] Boys. bus is here!
- [cheering]

616
00:38:59.916 --> 00:39:02.166
Excellent. The bus has arrived.

617
00:39:03.750 --> 00:39:04.750
Captain.

618
00:39:07.750 --> 00:39:08.750
Captain Shankar.

619
00:39:09.541 --> 00:39:11.375
Excuse me. Captain. I have some questions.

620
00:39:12.083 --> 00:39:13.083
Ladies.

621
00:39:14.125 --> 00:39:16.791
I apologize on behalf of my country
for your ordeal.

622
00:39:17.750 --> 00:39:18.791
If you would follow me.

623
00:39:19.750 --> 00:39:22.166
Captain. the young man
in your care. Vijay Rai.

624
00:39:22.250 --> 00:39:23.250
What about him?

625
00:39:24.666 --> 00:39:26.125
- This way.
- May I see him?

626
00:39:27.000 --> 00:39:28.000
You'll miss your bus.

627
00:39:28.625 --> 00:39:29.916
I can arrange a car service.

628
00:39:30.875 --> 00:39:32.333
And the reason. if I may ask.

629
00:39:33.333 --> 00:39:35.166
We all went through
an ordeal this morning.

630
00:39:35.250 --> 00:39:36.333
I'd like to know for whom.

631
00:39:37.791 --> 00:39:39.375
Hmm. I understand.

632
00:39:39.916 --> 00:39:42.250
Unfortunately.
Mr. Rai is still unconscious.

633
00:39:42.916 --> 00:39:45.708
- Your lieutenant said otherwise.
- My lieutenant was mistaken.

634
00:39:46.791 --> 00:39:49.625
Tell me. How often
do provincial police patrol here?

635
00:39:49.708 --> 00:39:53.708
[tense music playing]

636
00:39:53.791 --> 00:39:55.071
I don't understand the question.

637
00:39:56.291 --> 00:39:57.916
Couldn't be more than once a day.

638
00:39:59.666 --> 00:40:00.666
I mean. what luck.

639
00:40:01.750 --> 00:40:03.083
That you arrived when you did.

640
00:40:06.083 --> 00:40:07.500
Right. [Inhales]

641
00:40:08.041 --> 00:40:09.125
I can get his email.

642
00:40:09.916 --> 00:40:11.041
Send him a get well note.

643
00:40:12.083 --> 00:40:13.416
With a smiley face emoji.

644
00:40:14.500 --> 00:40:15.583
[man 8] Let's go.

645
00:40:16.583 --> 00:40:17.583
Come on. Dad.

646
00:40:21.125 --> 00:40:22.208
Just a second. honey.

647
00:40:23.250 --> 00:40:29.250
[foreboding music playing]

648
00:40:32.000 --> 00:40:33.333
[shed door closes]

649
00:40:36.416 --> 00:40:37.666
[pot hisses]

650
00:40:37.750 --> 00:40:41.458
I invest ten million dollars fees
and engineering studies.

651
00:40:44.458 --> 00:40:46.833
Waiting for a family of idiots
to do the right thing.

652
00:40:46.916 --> 00:40:47.916
[chair clangs]

653
00:40:48.416 --> 00:40:55.166
[foreboding music continues]

654
00:40:56.166 --> 00:40:57.291
[mobile keys clacking]

655
00:40:59.333 --> 00:41:00.333
"See you soon".

656
00:41:01.708 --> 00:41:02.708
That means...

657
00:41:03.916 --> 00:41:05.041
few hours travel.

658
00:41:05.583 --> 00:41:06.583
A day at most.

659
00:41:09.666 --> 00:41:10.666
He's here now.

660
00:41:12.208 --> 00:41:13.288
Somewhere in the mountains.

661
00:41:16.041 --> 00:41:17.041
Where?

662
00:41:18.875 --> 00:41:20.291
Where is your father. Vijay?

663
00:41:21.666 --> 00:41:22.666
He won't sell to you.

664
00:41:24.333 --> 00:41:25.333
Then you will.

665
00:41:27.458 --> 00:41:28.500
Never.

666
00:41:28.583 --> 00:41:30.541
Then the government will
when you're all dead.

667
00:41:33.125 --> 00:41:34.583
How can you not see this. man?

668
00:41:36.583 --> 00:41:37.583
[grunts]

669
00:41:37.791 --> 00:41:42.250
[foreboding music continues]

670
00:41:45.375 --> 00:41:46.500
Don't take all day.

671
00:41:48.500 --> 00:41:49.375
[door closes]

672
00:41:49.458 --> 00:41:52.000
- [metal scrapes]
- [fire rumbles]

673
00:41:53.083 --> 00:41:54.458
[poker hisses]

674
00:41:54.541 --> 00:41:56.625
[grunts. gasps]

675
00:41:58.125 --> 00:41:59.583
[Spike] Right. yup. that's it.

676
00:42:01.541 --> 00:42:02.541
Finished?

677
00:42:03.416 --> 00:42:04.541
Almost.

678
00:42:07.708 --> 00:42:08.708
Everything okay?

679
00:42:10.625 --> 00:42:11.625
I'm not sure.

680
00:42:11.666 --> 00:42:14.000
[footsteps approaching]

681
00:42:15.083 --> 00:42:16.291
Something's not right here.

682
00:42:17.208 --> 00:42:19.625
- What's the problem?
- We haven't formally met.

683
00:42:20.166 --> 00:42:21.666
- Mike.
- Evan Myers.

684
00:42:21.750 --> 00:42:23.310
- Let me give you a hand.
- Yes. Thanks.

685
00:42:24.041 --> 00:42:26.791
I represent a number
of Human Rights Watchdog groups.

686
00:42:27.291 --> 00:42:30.458
A man named Rudra Yash wants to dam
the river up there.

687
00:42:30.541 --> 00:42:33.000
A local family. the Rai's.
won't sell him the land.

688
00:42:33.458 --> 00:42:37.375
The grandfather. Raj Rai.
just died in a horrific bus accident.

689
00:42:38.250 --> 00:42:40.458
It was in the...
it was in the Kathmandu Post.

690
00:42:41.333 --> 00:42:44.833
I read the article.
His bus went off East Traverse.

691
00:42:44.916 --> 00:42:48.125
[chuckles] To which I say. bullshit.

692
00:42:49.916 --> 00:42:50.916
Why. Spike?

693
00:42:52.041 --> 00:42:56.083
Well. there's never been one bus go off
the East Traverse in the dry season.

694
00:42:56.166 --> 00:42:57.291
- Not a one.
- Right.

695
00:42:57.833 --> 00:42:58.833
Now get this.

696
00:42:58.916 --> 00:43:01.250
Raj Rai's son. Ganesh.
is apparently missing.

697
00:43:02.250 --> 00:43:03.750
And his grandson. Vijay...

698
00:43:04.666 --> 00:43:06.750
is the young man
you just saved from kidnappers.

699
00:43:07.125 --> 00:43:08.791
- [bus horn honking]
- [engine starts]

700
00:43:08.875 --> 00:43:09.875
[Tonya] Hello?

701
00:43:09.958 --> 00:43:11.291
Are you coming?

702
00:43:11.833 --> 00:43:13.583
Tell them to go ahead. Dhani. Please.

703
00:43:14.166 --> 00:43:16.416
Keep talking. Professor.
You've got my attention.

704
00:43:16.500 --> 00:43:18.416
The kidnappers were rendezvousing here.

705
00:43:19.166 --> 00:43:20.166
Who with?

706
00:43:20.875 --> 00:43:22.267
Who just turned up out of the blue?

707
00:43:22.291 --> 00:43:26.083
[foreboding music playing]

708
00:43:26.166 --> 00:43:28.708
- Oh. you... You're not saying...?
- Police. yes.

709
00:43:29.583 --> 00:43:30.583
Bugger. me.

710
00:43:31.666 --> 00:43:33.291
Dhani. you catching this?

711
00:43:33.375 --> 00:43:34.416
It is possible.

712
00:43:35.083 --> 00:43:37.166
Rudra Yash is Kathmandu Mafia.

713
00:43:37.625 --> 00:43:40.750
Thugs and parasites.
They buy judges and police.

714
00:43:41.541 --> 00:43:43.083
What do you suggest we do. Professor?

715
00:43:44.208 --> 00:43:45.375
Demand to see Vijay Rai.

716
00:43:45.458 --> 00:43:47.916
[foreboding music continues]

717
00:43:48.000 --> 00:43:49.875
- You are poking a dragon.
- [chuckles]

718
00:43:50.250 --> 00:43:53.125
- I've poked one or two before. trust me.
- I want answers.

719
00:43:54.125 --> 00:43:56.708
You may need a translator. Dhani. can you?

720
00:43:59.416 --> 00:44:00.416
Yes.

721
00:44:00.666 --> 00:44:01.708
Stay here. okay?

722
00:44:01.791 --> 00:44:03.666
Yeah. son. I'll look after her for you.

723
00:44:03.750 --> 00:44:05.830
- Don't worry. she'll be all right.
- [Myers] Thanks.

724
00:44:09.541 --> 00:44:10.666
[Starr] Dad!

725
00:44:13.583 --> 00:44:14.583
Be careful.

726
00:44:19.250 --> 00:44:21.041
[footsteps approaching]

727
00:44:24.833 --> 00:44:27.458
Um. tell him we want to see Vijay Rai.

728
00:44:27.541 --> 00:44:31.625
- [speaking Nepali]
- [speaking Nepali]

729
00:44:31.708 --> 00:44:33.791
[speaking Nepali]

730
00:44:33.875 --> 00:44:35.166
- No.
- [Vijay screaming]

731
00:44:36.000 --> 00:44:37.541
- [Mike grunts]
- [thud]

732
00:44:37.625 --> 00:44:40.833
- [body thuds]
- [dramatic music playing]

733
00:44:40.916 --> 00:44:41.916
[Mike] Come on.

734
00:44:44.208 --> 00:44:45.666
- [poker hisses]
- [Vijay screams]

735
00:44:45.750 --> 00:44:48.375
[Shankar] This is not going to end.

736
00:44:48.458 --> 00:44:49.625
- [thud]
- [Vijay screaming]

737
00:44:50.916 --> 00:44:52.666
[Shankar] We're gonna be here all night.

738
00:44:53.041 --> 00:44:54.142
- [poker sizzles]
- [Vijay groans]

739
00:44:54.166 --> 00:44:56.125
[gasping]

740
00:44:56.208 --> 00:44:57.875
Where is your father?

741
00:44:57.958 --> 00:44:59.125
[Vijay whimpering]

742
00:44:59.208 --> 00:45:02.416
Where is your father?

743
00:45:02.500 --> 00:45:03.875
I'll call the American Embassy.

744
00:45:04.416 --> 00:45:06.166
- [Vijay screaming]
- They took our phones.

745
00:45:06.250 --> 00:45:07.434
[Myers] We'll find one in the village.

746
00:45:07.458 --> 00:45:09.916
I'm not looking for phones
while that kid's being tortured.

747
00:45:11.708 --> 00:45:14.208
Wait here. Professor. Dhani. come with me.

748
00:45:14.291 --> 00:45:15.541
[sinister music playing]

749
00:45:15.625 --> 00:45:16.625
[Vijay groans]

750
00:45:18.875 --> 00:45:20.315
[Shankar] We have your phone. Vijay.

751
00:45:21.208 --> 00:45:24.041
Your text message to your father
said you were meeting.

752
00:45:24.125 --> 00:45:25.208
Now tell me where.

753
00:45:26.291 --> 00:45:27.931
[Vijay gasps]
- Where are you meeting him?

754
00:45:28.166 --> 00:45:30.458
[Vijay gasping. groaning]

755
00:45:30.541 --> 00:45:33.041
- Where is your father. Vijay?
- [Vijay groans]

756
00:45:33.958 --> 00:45:34.958
[gun cocks]

757
00:45:35.000 --> 00:45:37.875
- [Vijay coughs]
- [sinister music intensifies]

758
00:45:45.458 --> 00:45:46.666
Throw it down.

759
00:45:50.541 --> 00:45:51.541
[metal poker clangs]

760
00:45:52.750 --> 00:45:53.916
[knife cutting. slices]

761
00:45:54.000 --> 00:45:56.500
- You don't know who you're dealing with.
- [Mike] Sure I do.

762
00:45:56.583 --> 00:45:58.666
You're Police Captain Shankar.

763
00:45:59.750 --> 00:46:02.875
There was me thinking the policemen
were supposed to help the victim.

764
00:46:02.958 --> 00:46:04.000
[pot hisses]

765
00:46:04.083 --> 00:46:05.083
[door opens]

766
00:46:06.125 --> 00:46:08.500
[Rudra] Everyone. calm down. please.

767
00:46:08.875 --> 00:46:13.041
[sinister music continues]

768
00:46:13.125 --> 00:46:15.208
Welcome to Kodari Rug Factory.

769
00:46:17.708 --> 00:46:19.000
At least tell me your names.

770
00:46:20.375 --> 00:46:22.333
If we're going to settle this
with firearms.

771
00:46:23.125 --> 00:46:25.805
we should at least know the names
of the people pulling the trigger.

772
00:46:26.833 --> 00:46:28.125
[Myers] My name is Evan Myers.

773
00:46:28.208 --> 00:46:34.333
[sinister music continues]

774
00:46:34.416 --> 00:46:36.666
I represent
the United States Department of State.

775
00:46:40.000 --> 00:46:41.541
What a group we suddenly are.

776
00:46:42.583 --> 00:46:45.083
In 24 hours.
every human rights organization

777
00:46:45.166 --> 00:46:46.541
in the world will know about this.

778
00:46:46.625 --> 00:46:48.250
You have a lot of explaining to do.

779
00:46:52.791 --> 00:46:53.791
Do I?

780
00:46:55.416 --> 00:46:57.958
I called the United States Embassy.
20 minutes ago.

781
00:46:58.041 --> 00:47:00.721
- There'll be two Blackhawk helicopters...
- [Rudra] No. you didn't.

782
00:47:01.291 --> 00:47:02.375
You didn't call anyone.

783
00:47:02.458 --> 00:47:03.958
[music stops]

784
00:47:06.041 --> 00:47:07.250
[gunshot]

785
00:47:07.958 --> 00:47:11.416
- [dramatic music playing]
- [gunshots firing]

786
00:47:11.500 --> 00:47:13.375
[gunfire]

787
00:47:13.458 --> 00:47:16.083
[dramatic music continues]

788
00:47:22.000 --> 00:47:23.041
[Mike] Run!

789
00:47:23.458 --> 00:47:24.458
Now. run!

790
00:47:24.833 --> 00:47:25.875
[Dhani] Go.

791
00:47:29.791 --> 00:47:31.916
[Dhani] Spike. start the bus.

792
00:47:32.291 --> 00:47:33.559
- [Spike] What in the?
- [Dhani] Start the bus.

793
00:47:33.583 --> 00:47:36.083
Get the tools.
Bloody tools. Get them in the bus.

794
00:47:36.583 --> 00:47:38.750
- Hurry up!
- Where's my father?

795
00:47:40.083 --> 00:47:41.750
Get in! Fast!

796
00:47:43.666 --> 00:47:45.416
[engine starting]

797
00:47:45.500 --> 00:47:48.916
[dramatic music continues]

798
00:47:49.416 --> 00:47:50.416
[groans]

799
00:47:53.375 --> 00:47:54.625
- [grunts]
- [body thuds]

800
00:47:54.708 --> 00:48:00.041
[dramatic music intensifies]

801
00:48:00.125 --> 00:48:03.750
- [indistinct clamoring]
- [horn honking]

802
00:48:03.833 --> 00:48:05.833
- [brakes hiss]
- [engine revs]

803
00:48:06.625 --> 00:48:11.500
[dramatic music continues]

804
00:48:13.000 --> 00:48:14.375
Where's my father?

805
00:48:16.375 --> 00:48:17.791
[agitatedly] Where's my father?

806
00:48:18.166 --> 00:48:19.166
He didn't make it.

807
00:48:19.416 --> 00:48:20.816
What do you mean he didn't make it?

808
00:48:23.750 --> 00:48:24.750
[brakes screech]

809
00:48:24.833 --> 00:48:28.791
[dramatic music continues]

810
00:48:30.583 --> 00:48:33.500
[dramatic music crescendos]

811
00:48:33.583 --> 00:48:34.583
He's dead.

812
00:48:34.625 --> 00:48:40.375
[suspenseful music playing]

813
00:48:41.083 --> 00:48:42.125
Do not shoot the boy.

814
00:48:49.208 --> 00:48:50.583
Oh. shit!

815
00:48:50.666 --> 00:48:54.000
[suspenseful music continues]

816
00:48:54.083 --> 00:48:55.291
Shit!

817
00:48:57.250 --> 00:48:58.500
Everybody down!

818
00:48:59.958 --> 00:49:01.833
- [engine revs]
- [clanging]

819
00:49:08.041 --> 00:49:10.500
[gunfire]

820
00:49:11.500 --> 00:49:13.750
[gunfire]

821
00:49:15.541 --> 00:49:17.375
- [engine revs]
- [gunshots]

822
00:49:20.625 --> 00:49:26.166
[suspenseful music continues]

823
00:49:30.125 --> 00:49:31.166
[Mike grunts]

824
00:49:36.958 --> 00:49:43.958
- [suspenseful music continues]
- [objects clattering]

825
00:49:50.375 --> 00:49:51.416
[engine accelerating]

826
00:49:52.208 --> 00:49:57.916
[suspenseful music intensifies]

827
00:49:59.666 --> 00:50:00.666
[Mike] Hold on.

828
00:50:05.916 --> 00:50:08.666
Give me a blade. a knife. anything!

829
00:50:10.000 --> 00:50:11.583
- [engine revs]
- [tires screech]

830
00:50:11.666 --> 00:50:16.958
[suspenseful music continues]

831
00:50:17.041 --> 00:50:18.500
[tires screech]

832
00:50:24.083 --> 00:50:26.291
[ropes whipping]

833
00:50:26.375 --> 00:50:29.250
[loud clanging]

834
00:50:31.166 --> 00:50:33.708
[loud clanging]

835
00:50:33.791 --> 00:50:34.791
[grunts]

836
00:50:36.000 --> 00:50:39.083
[suspenseful music crescendos]

837
00:50:42.750 --> 00:50:47.416
[ominous music playing]

838
00:50:55.291 --> 00:51:01.291
[ominous music continues]

839
00:51:06.458 --> 00:51:07.458
[exhales sharply]

840
00:51:12.583 --> 00:51:15.500
[Spike wheezing]

841
00:51:19.833 --> 00:51:24.291
[bus engine rumbling]

842
00:51:25.041 --> 00:51:30.125
[speaking Nepali]

843
00:51:31.666 --> 00:51:35.375
[speaking Nepali]

844
00:51:35.458 --> 00:51:39.166
[speaking Nepali]

845
00:51:39.250 --> 00:51:41.666
- [engine revs]
- [pipes bang]

846
00:51:41.750 --> 00:51:44.083
[speaking Nepali]

847
00:51:49.958 --> 00:51:51.500
[zipper unzipping]

848
00:52:06.625 --> 00:52:07.625
[Starr sniffles]

849
00:52:22.041 --> 00:52:22.916
How is he?

850
00:52:23.000 --> 00:52:25.500
[sinister music playing]

851
00:52:25.583 --> 00:52:26.583
He's dying.

852
00:52:27.833 --> 00:52:29.333
[crane whirring]

853
00:52:30.333 --> 00:52:33.166
[crane beeps]

854
00:52:37.541 --> 00:52:40.875
- [truck door closes]
- [truck engine starting]

855
00:52:44.083 --> 00:52:48.833
[engines revving]

856
00:52:48.916 --> 00:52:55.291
[sinister music continues]

857
00:53:01.875 --> 00:53:03.000
[music fades]

858
00:53:03.083 --> 00:53:04.083
Vijay.

859
00:53:04.333 --> 00:53:05.583
Right turn back to the village.

860
00:53:06.000 --> 00:53:08.291
Left turn Chinese border. Safe there.

861
00:53:08.375 --> 00:53:10.250
Construction workers
for the belt and road.

862
00:53:10.333 --> 00:53:11.958
Soldiers. Hot food.

863
00:53:12.958 --> 00:53:14.083
Which way is your father?

864
00:53:16.125 --> 00:53:18.375
Left. Across the Annapurna Highlands.

865
00:53:18.958 --> 00:53:20.500
But this is the long way.

866
00:53:20.916 --> 00:53:22.083
It's much faster by mule.

867
00:53:22.583 --> 00:53:25.833
Great. Let's hitch up the team
I got back there.

868
00:53:29.166 --> 00:53:32.291
- I forgive your American sarcasm there.
- It's Irish sarcasm.

869
00:53:32.375 --> 00:53:33.625
What are we dealing with here?

870
00:53:34.333 --> 00:53:35.875
Very steep and very icy.

871
00:53:36.208 --> 00:53:37.625
Right up my alley.

872
00:53:38.000 --> 00:53:39.416
It's called the Road To The Sky.

873
00:53:39.958 --> 00:53:43.750
It's said Siddhartha came this way
on his quest to find enlightenment.

874
00:53:44.250 --> 00:53:45.875
[Spike] Well. I ain't no Siddhartha.

875
00:53:45.958 --> 00:53:49.333
I'm as enlightened as I'm gonna get.
Let me off the bus. I'm not dying here.

876
00:53:49.416 --> 00:53:50.958
[Spike] Get me out of here.

877
00:53:51.041 --> 00:53:52.041
Get me off the bus.

878
00:53:54.250 --> 00:53:56.208
[Mike grunting]

879
00:53:57.291 --> 00:53:58.291
Yeah.

880
00:53:59.333 --> 00:54:00.833
Yeah. That'll do.

881
00:54:00.916 --> 00:54:03.375
- I'll get you there. You'll be right.
- Yeah. right here.

882
00:54:03.458 --> 00:54:05.375
- That's it.
- I got ya. Argh.

883
00:54:06.125 --> 00:54:08.208
- [Spike groans]
- [winds blowing]

884
00:54:11.333 --> 00:54:12.916
[Spike] No worries.

885
00:54:17.458 --> 00:54:18.458
See you down the river.

886
00:54:19.250 --> 00:54:20.541
Yes. Spike.

887
00:54:22.291 --> 00:54:24.500
[Spike sighs. groans]

888
00:54:28.458 --> 00:54:29.458
Down the river.

889
00:54:30.625 --> 00:54:31.625
[Spike] Hmm.

890
00:54:39.791 --> 00:54:41.375
Four rounds. Okay.

891
00:54:42.916 --> 00:54:44.333
Better than one. I suppose.

892
00:54:45.375 --> 00:54:48.625
Are you sure about this?
Say the word. we'll take you back in.

893
00:54:48.708 --> 00:54:50.625
I'm not dying on my own bus.

894
00:54:52.791 --> 00:54:54.458
I'd rather die out here.

895
00:54:54.541 --> 00:54:59.875
[somber music playing]

896
00:55:05.416 --> 00:55:06.916
[Spike] Down the river. Dhani.

897
00:55:07.375 --> 00:55:08.541
Down the river.

898
00:55:11.166 --> 00:55:12.166
Bye. Spike.

899
00:55:15.083 --> 00:55:16.000
[Spike] Yeah.

900
00:55:16.083 --> 00:55:22.125
- [somber music continues]
- [winds blowing]

901
00:55:36.916 --> 00:55:37.916
You know...

902
00:55:39.000 --> 00:55:40.791
my late brother used to say...

903
00:55:41.916 --> 00:55:43.166
"life is for the living."

904
00:55:45.041 --> 00:55:46.166
We have to go on.

905
00:55:47.333 --> 00:55:48.333
All of us.

906
00:55:51.250 --> 00:55:52.708
[engine starting]

907
00:56:01.583 --> 00:56:08.416
[somber music continues]

908
00:56:20.166 --> 00:56:21.166
[engine stops]

909
00:56:21.250 --> 00:56:22.500
[music fades]

910
00:56:27.500 --> 00:56:29.166
[wind whistles]

911
00:56:30.083 --> 00:56:32.125
[Mike] 40 percent grade. Iced over.

912
00:56:33.291 --> 00:56:34.833
Hairpin turn at the bottom.

913
00:56:35.208 --> 00:56:36.333
It's suicide.

914
00:56:37.750 --> 00:56:39.833
No suicide. Mike. We use this.

915
00:56:42.750 --> 00:56:45.041
[wind blowing]

916
00:56:45.125 --> 00:56:46.125
Chinese?

917
00:56:46.458 --> 00:56:49.416
[Vijay] Belt and Road Initiative.
For their construction equipment.

918
00:56:51.708 --> 00:56:52.708
[Mike] Let me guess.

919
00:56:53.625 --> 00:56:55.833
- Point your vehicle down the grade.
- [Vijay] Check.

920
00:56:55.916 --> 00:56:58.166
- [Mike] Hook the winch to the bumper.
- [Vijay] Check.

921
00:56:58.250 --> 00:57:00.125
[Mike] Set the rate of descent. Get in.

922
00:57:00.875 --> 00:57:02.875
- Release the brake.
- Check. Piece of pie.

923
00:57:03.458 --> 00:57:05.333
Cake. Vijay. Piece of cake.

924
00:57:06.625 --> 00:57:08.375
- [Mike] One. two. three.
- [rope whirrs]

925
00:57:08.875 --> 00:57:11.166
One. two. three. One. two. three.

926
00:57:11.250 --> 00:57:12.666
[winch rattling]

927
00:57:14.166 --> 00:57:15.166
Hold it.

928
00:57:15.250 --> 00:57:19.541
[dramatic music playing]

929
00:57:19.625 --> 00:57:20.750
[Mike] Everybody ready?

930
00:57:21.083 --> 00:57:22.226
- [Vijay] Dhani?
- [Dhani] Do it!

931
00:57:22.250 --> 00:57:25.750
[Mike] Get it. Come on!
- [machine whirring]

932
00:57:27.458 --> 00:57:28.333
[Dhani grunts]

933
00:57:28.416 --> 00:57:34.166
[dramatic music continues]

934
00:57:34.250 --> 00:57:35.610
- [brakes gas]
- [handbrake cranks]

935
00:57:40.041 --> 00:57:42.333
- [cable whips]
- [bus rumbles]

936
00:57:45.666 --> 00:57:48.041
[winch whirrs]

937
00:57:48.125 --> 00:57:52.833
[euphoric music playing]

938
00:57:54.916 --> 00:57:57.291
[dramatic music continues]

939
00:57:57.375 --> 00:57:59.166
Look ma. no hands. [Chuckles]

940
00:57:59.833 --> 00:58:00.875
Piece of cake.

941
00:58:00.958 --> 00:58:07.875
[dramatic music continues]

942
00:58:13.750 --> 00:58:20.125
[dramatic music continues]

943
00:58:20.208 --> 00:58:22.041
[bus thuds. rattles]

944
00:58:22.458 --> 00:58:24.250
- What the...
- What's happening?

945
00:58:24.333 --> 00:58:26.208
[winch clangs]

946
00:58:26.291 --> 00:58:27.416
What's happening?

947
00:58:29.375 --> 00:58:32.916
[winch spluttering]

948
00:58:34.083 --> 00:58:35.291
The engine's seized.

949
00:58:35.666 --> 00:58:36.666
[winch whirrs. whines]

950
00:58:36.750 --> 00:58:38.226
- [Starr] What are we gonna do?
- [Vijay] I don't know.

951
00:58:38.250 --> 00:58:40.250
- Don't ask me.
- [Starr] Well. we can't stay here.

952
00:58:41.166 --> 00:58:42.041
- Vijay.
- Yes?

953
00:58:42.125 --> 00:58:43.166
Yank the brake.

954
00:58:43.250 --> 00:58:44.291
Where... where is it?

955
00:58:44.375 --> 00:58:46.375
Right... right hand side
of the driver's seat.

956
00:58:46.458 --> 00:58:47.458
Okay.

957
00:58:48.291 --> 00:58:50.458
- What are you doing?
- [Mike] Releasing that cable.

958
00:58:50.541 --> 00:58:53.333
- [Vijay] If we do. we die.
- If we don't. we die.

959
00:58:54.708 --> 00:58:56.000
Can you make that turn?

960
00:58:56.083 --> 00:58:58.166
It's... it's 50-50 at best.

961
00:58:58.250 --> 00:58:59.375
Okay.

962
00:58:59.750 --> 00:59:01.291
Good enough. Give it to me.

963
00:59:02.666 --> 00:59:06.416
[dramatic music playing]

964
00:59:06.500 --> 00:59:07.500
[grunts]

965
00:59:09.583 --> 00:59:10.583
Everybody ready?

966
00:59:13.041 --> 00:59:14.041
[Dhani] Yes. ready!

967
00:59:16.416 --> 00:59:18.083
- [grunts]
- [metal clangs]

968
00:59:18.166 --> 00:59:22.958
[dramatic music continues]

969
00:59:23.041 --> 00:59:24.750
- [grunts]
- [cable whips]

970
00:59:25.791 --> 00:59:26.625
[Vijay] Bus is going down.

971
00:59:26.708 --> 00:59:32.000
[dramatic music intensifies]

972
00:59:32.458 --> 00:59:33.458
[groans]

973
00:59:37.791 --> 00:59:39.708
[gears grinding]

974
00:59:42.625 --> 00:59:44.583
[Vijay] Mike. we're not gonna make it.

975
00:59:45.666 --> 00:59:46.666
Hang on!

976
00:59:50.125 --> 00:59:51.208
[indistinct chatter]

977
00:59:51.291 --> 00:59:58.208
[dramatic music continues]

978
01:00:01.375 --> 01:00:02.875
[brakes grinding]

979
01:00:02.958 --> 01:00:04.166
[Starr] Whoa!

980
01:00:09.958 --> 01:00:10.958
[Starr] Oh. my God.

981
01:00:13.625 --> 01:00:15.745
- [Starr] Oh. my God. Mike!
- [Mike] Hold on. Hold on.

982
01:00:19.041 --> 01:00:22.000
[dramatic music fades]

983
01:00:22.083 --> 01:00:24.208
Everybody okay? Speak to me!

984
01:00:24.750 --> 01:00:26.333
- [Dhani] Yes.
- [Vijay] Yeah.

985
01:00:26.416 --> 01:00:29.375
[all groaning]

986
01:00:34.125 --> 01:00:38.416
[wind whistling]

987
01:00:42.791 --> 01:00:43.833
Shit.

988
01:00:44.250 --> 01:00:46.625
Without an axle. the Kiwi Express...

989
01:00:47.416 --> 01:00:48.791
is officially dead.

990
01:00:48.875 --> 01:00:50.476
[Vijay] So are we
if we have to go on foot.

991
01:00:50.500 --> 01:00:52.000
We tried. I'm sorry.

992
01:00:52.958 --> 01:00:53.958
I'm sorry.

993
01:00:55.916 --> 01:00:57.000
[Dhani] You saved our life.

994
01:00:58.458 --> 01:00:59.791
If it wasn't for you...

995
01:01:00.416 --> 01:01:02.291
we'd be at the bottom of that cliff.

996
01:01:04.083 --> 01:01:06.708
[wind whistling]

997
01:01:10.125 --> 01:01:12.000
Anyone have a pair of binoculars?

998
01:01:14.875 --> 01:01:17.833
[footsteps receding]

999
01:01:25.916 --> 01:01:29.083
[wind blowing. whistling]

1000
01:01:29.166 --> 01:01:35.250
[soft inspirational music playing]

1001
01:01:35.333 --> 01:01:38.083
- [inspirational music fades]
- [dramatic music playing]

1002
01:01:38.541 --> 01:01:39.791
We're in business. kids.

1003
01:01:41.166 --> 01:01:42.375
We'll get her upright.

1004
01:01:42.458 --> 01:01:43.875
- And Vijay?
- [Vijay] Yeah?

1005
01:01:43.958 --> 01:01:46.291
I want you to skim the tires
off those rims.

1006
01:01:48.750 --> 01:01:50.708
We're gonna need
some of that broken guardrail.

1007
01:01:51.041 --> 01:01:52.500
Um. why?

1008
01:01:52.583 --> 01:01:53.583
Why. Mike?

1009
01:01:54.583 --> 01:01:58.333
The Kiwi Express is about to be reborn.
Come on.

1010
01:02:02.500 --> 01:02:04.125
- [dramatic music fades]
- [Spike groans]

1011
01:02:05.333 --> 01:02:09.333
- [wind blowing]
- [Spike gasping]

1012
01:02:09.416 --> 01:02:10.708
[groans]

1013
01:02:14.583 --> 01:02:16.208
[quivering]

1014
01:02:16.875 --> 01:02:17.875
[Starr] Okay.

1015
01:02:17.958 --> 01:02:23.958
[suspenseful music playing]

1016
01:02:35.083 --> 01:02:37.125
[creaking. thud]

1017
01:02:39.958 --> 01:02:42.000
[suspenseful music fades]

1018
01:02:42.083 --> 01:02:44.041
[car engines revving]

1019
01:02:44.125 --> 01:02:47.333
[ominous music playing]

1020
01:02:47.416 --> 01:02:48.416
[groans]

1021
01:02:49.625 --> 01:02:50.666
[grunts]

1022
01:02:50.750 --> 01:02:53.416
[engines revving]

1023
01:02:54.291 --> 01:02:55.208
[grunts]

1024
01:02:55.291 --> 01:02:57.250
[gunshots]

1025
01:03:03.791 --> 01:03:04.708
[car door opens]

1026
01:03:04.791 --> 01:03:05.791
[sighs]

1027
01:03:06.291 --> 01:03:08.041
[doors opening. closing]

1028
01:03:10.750 --> 01:03:15.458
[ominous music turns tense]

1029
01:03:15.541 --> 01:03:17.208
[music fades]

1030
01:03:20.541 --> 01:03:25.958
Torturing defenseless kids
is very bad karma. mate.

1031
01:03:27.166 --> 01:03:28.750
Catch up with you in the next life.

1032
01:03:29.458 --> 01:03:30.541
I'm an atheist.

1033
01:03:31.500 --> 01:03:33.625
It's easy to live as an atheist.

1034
01:03:35.083 --> 01:03:37.000
Not so easy to die as one.

1035
01:03:38.541 --> 01:03:39.541
You'll see.

1036
01:03:43.125 --> 01:03:45.351
- [Mike] Vijay? Need two more of these.
- [Vijay] Yeah? Got it.

1037
01:03:45.375 --> 01:03:47.875
[suspenseful music playing]

1038
01:03:47.958 --> 01:03:49.078
- Take these.
- [Dhani] Yeah.

1039
01:03:51.875 --> 01:03:53.958
[whirring]

1040
01:03:56.250 --> 01:04:02.791
[suspenseful music continues]

1041
01:04:08.083 --> 01:04:09.166
[Mike] Dhani?

1042
01:04:09.500 --> 01:04:12.083
These military run-flat tires
will come in handy.

1043
01:04:17.291 --> 01:04:20.333
[suspenseful music fades]

1044
01:04:20.416 --> 01:04:21.416
Dhani?

1045
01:04:21.958 --> 01:04:23.625
[engines revving]

1046
01:04:29.375 --> 01:04:36.000
[ominous music playing]

1047
01:04:36.083 --> 01:04:37.541
[doors closing]

1048
01:04:38.791 --> 01:04:43.166
[winch whirring]

1049
01:04:44.500 --> 01:04:46.625
[winch sputters. hisses]

1050
01:04:47.125 --> 01:04:48.365
[Shankar] The clutch is burned.

1051
01:04:49.166 --> 01:04:50.875
[hissing]

1052
01:04:52.333 --> 01:04:53.333
How long to fix it?

1053
01:04:53.958 --> 01:04:55.291
At least two hours.

1054
01:05:02.375 --> 01:05:04.875
[Kiwi Express idling]

1055
01:05:04.958 --> 01:05:06.541
[engine revving]

1056
01:05:06.625 --> 01:05:08.875
[whirring. squeaking]

1057
01:05:13.375 --> 01:05:15.250
[tools rattling]

1058
01:05:15.333 --> 01:05:16.833
You know how to use one of these?

1059
01:05:21.041 --> 01:05:22.708
Yeah. it's basically twelve.

1060
01:05:22.791 --> 01:05:25.500
Yeah. four. four. four.

1061
01:05:29.458 --> 01:05:32.750
[Dhani] This isn't the Himalayan trip
you expected.

1062
01:05:34.083 --> 01:05:35.833
Tides come. tides go.

1063
01:05:36.833 --> 01:05:39.500
You can't stop them.
You gotta go with the flow.

1064
01:05:40.083 --> 01:05:43.125
- The <i>Upanishads</i>?
- <i>Upanishads.</i> yeah.

1065
01:05:43.583 --> 01:05:47.166
[chuckles] Spoken like
a true lapsed Catholic.

1066
01:05:47.250 --> 01:05:48.916
- [chuckling]
- [grinding]

1067
01:05:49.583 --> 01:05:51.083
[Vijay] Pull on that.
- Okay.

1068
01:05:52.125 --> 01:05:54.833
[wind blowing]

1069
01:05:55.958 --> 01:05:57.041
Tell me about your family.

1070
01:05:57.833 --> 01:05:58.833
Your mother.

1071
01:05:59.125 --> 01:06:00.125
Your grandparents.

1072
01:06:01.750 --> 01:06:02.750
Um...

1073
01:06:04.041 --> 01:06:05.541
Well. my grandparents are dead.

1074
01:06:08.000 --> 01:06:09.416
Mom's a bit of a mess.

1075
01:06:10.916 --> 01:06:11.916
Dad...

1076
01:06:15.958 --> 01:06:17.083
Well. you know about that.

1077
01:06:18.041 --> 01:06:19.041
They were divorced.

1078
01:06:21.708 --> 01:06:22.708
Makes you feel sad.

1079
01:06:23.000 --> 01:06:26.375
[somber music playing]

1080
01:06:26.458 --> 01:06:27.583
Of course it makes me sad.

1081
01:06:30.958 --> 01:06:32.118
You'll see your father again.

1082
01:06:32.166 --> 01:06:37.916
[somber music continues]

1083
01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:39.166
You ever been married?

1084
01:06:39.791 --> 01:06:40.958
[Dhani] Once.

1085
01:06:41.583 --> 01:06:42.875
Youthful mistake.

1086
01:06:44.875 --> 01:06:46.708
I wouldn't know anything about those.

1087
01:06:52.458 --> 01:06:53.750
[clang. thud]

1088
01:06:53.833 --> 01:06:58.000
[dramatic music playing]

1089
01:06:58.083 --> 01:06:59.083
[Shankar] Don't worry.

1090
01:06:59.541 --> 01:07:02.125
We'll probably find them dead
in one of those ravines.

1091
01:07:03.000 --> 01:07:05.083
You can afford not to worry. I can't.

1092
01:07:05.458 --> 01:07:08.083
Rudra. we will get Vijay and Ganesh Rai.

1093
01:07:10.166 --> 01:07:12.791
- Yeah. that's what you said in Kodari.
- [lever clattering]

1094
01:07:14.083 --> 01:07:19.541
[dramatic music playing]

1095
01:07:26.875 --> 01:07:33.083
[dramatic music continues]

1096
01:07:35.208 --> 01:07:36.208
- Go!
- [Dhani grunts]

1097
01:07:37.875 --> 01:07:39.291
[Mike] One. two. three. go!

1098
01:07:39.375 --> 01:07:40.416
[Dhani grunts]

1099
01:07:44.375 --> 01:07:47.458
- [dramatic music fades]
- [wind blows]

1100
01:07:48.791 --> 01:07:50.625
[Vijay] Next stop. my father's cabin.

1101
01:07:51.375 --> 01:07:52.375
Good deal.

1102
01:08:02.416 --> 01:08:03.416
[groans]

1103
01:08:03.500 --> 01:08:04.625
You okay?

1104
01:08:06.541 --> 01:08:07.750
Yeah. all good.

1105
01:08:08.916 --> 01:08:14.083
[suspenseful music playing]

1106
01:08:14.166 --> 01:08:15.291
[man 9] Car's ready. sir.

1107
01:08:18.000 --> 01:08:20.916
[keys beeping]

1108
01:08:25.208 --> 01:08:26.291
[mobile vibrating]

1109
01:08:26.375 --> 01:08:32.416
[suspenseful music continues]

1110
01:08:39.208 --> 01:08:40.208
Answer yes.

1111
01:08:40.583 --> 01:08:43.166
[keys beeping]

1112
01:08:43.541 --> 01:08:45.583
Add emojis. It looks more natural.

1113
01:08:46.166 --> 01:08:47.583
[mobile vibrates]

1114
01:08:51.250 --> 01:08:56.166
[suspenseful music continues]

1115
01:08:59.916 --> 01:09:03.291
[keys beeping]

1116
01:09:03.375 --> 01:09:04.458
[mobile vibrates]

1117
01:09:10.041 --> 01:09:12.416
[Shankar] The old fool fell for it. Reply.

1118
01:09:12.500 --> 01:09:14.708
[keys beeping]

1119
01:09:15.291 --> 01:09:16.291
[mobile beeps]

1120
01:09:22.375 --> 01:09:24.625
[motorbike engine idling]

1121
01:09:24.708 --> 01:09:25.875
Do you know where that is?

1122
01:09:27.083 --> 01:09:30.083
The old man is there.
Take him out and dispose of the body.

1123
01:09:31.041 --> 01:09:37.333
- [engine revving]
- [dramatic music playing]

1124
01:09:41.000 --> 01:09:43.625
[Kiwi Express accelerating]

1125
01:09:45.708 --> 01:09:52.708
[pensive music playing]

1126
01:09:57.625 --> 01:09:58.916
Welcome to the Highlands.

1127
01:10:00.708 --> 01:10:05.541
[dramatic music continues]

1128
01:10:11.583 --> 01:10:13.666
[dramatic music fades]

1129
01:10:19.708 --> 01:10:25.208
[ominous music playing]

1130
01:10:35.791 --> 01:10:42.166
[ominous music intensifies]

1131
01:10:46.250 --> 01:10:47.958
[footsteps approaching]

1132
01:10:48.375 --> 01:10:50.166
[match hisses]

1133
01:10:52.083 --> 01:10:58.625
[ominous music continues]

1134
01:11:01.250 --> 01:11:02.750
[thuds]

1135
01:11:03.916 --> 01:11:06.125
[ominous music crescendos]

1136
01:11:06.208 --> 01:11:07.250
[gunshot]

1137
01:11:12.666 --> 01:11:16.875
[Kiwi Express decelerates]

1138
01:11:19.708 --> 01:11:22.250
[brakes squeaking]

1139
01:11:23.375 --> 01:11:26.458
[rattles]

1140
01:11:32.875 --> 01:11:33.875
[engine stops]

1141
01:11:34.458 --> 01:11:39.416
[fire crackling]

1142
01:11:39.500 --> 01:11:41.000
- [Dhani] Your father's?
- No. no.

1143
01:11:41.500 --> 01:11:42.833
My father is a mile further.

1144
01:11:43.625 --> 01:11:44.750
Then whose is that?

1145
01:11:45.166 --> 01:11:46.833
[Ganesh] That was our neighbor.

1146
01:11:48.083 --> 01:11:49.208
[speaking Hindi]

1147
01:11:49.708 --> 01:11:52.541
- [speaking Hindi]
- [Ganesh] My boy! [Speaking Hindi]

1148
01:11:53.250 --> 01:11:54.333
[speaking Hindi]

1149
01:11:54.416 --> 01:11:58.083
- [chuckles. sighs]
- [inspirational music playing]

1150
01:11:58.166 --> 01:11:59.833
- [speaking Hindi]
- [speaking Hindi]

1151
01:12:02.875 --> 01:12:05.333
How did you know
it was Rudra Yash texting and not me?

1152
01:12:05.416 --> 01:12:07.291
I send two emojis. I get one back.

1153
01:12:07.833 --> 01:12:09.291
I send one emoji. I get none back.

1154
01:12:09.666 --> 01:12:12.416
The code. remember?
So I sent one and I got one back.

1155
01:12:12.500 --> 01:12:14.375
So I knew he had your phone.

1156
01:12:14.458 --> 01:12:16.583
- It worked.
- [Ganesh] It worked. it worked.

1157
01:12:16.916 --> 01:12:18.036
Oh. my boy. [Speaking Hindi]

1158
01:12:18.416 --> 01:12:19.958
[speaking Hindi]

1159
01:12:20.041 --> 01:12:21.833
- These are your friends?
- Yes. Baba.

1160
01:12:22.875 --> 01:12:24.515
- This is Dhani.
- [Ganesh speaking Hindi]

1161
01:12:25.458 --> 01:12:26.333
- Hey.
- [Ganesh] Thank you so much.

1162
01:12:26.416 --> 01:12:27.708
- Dhani.
- And this is Starr.

1163
01:12:27.791 --> 01:12:28.831
- [Ganesh] Thank you.
- Hi.

1164
01:12:29.041 --> 01:12:30.226
- [Ganesh] Welcome. welcome.
- Thank you.

1165
01:12:30.250 --> 01:12:32.416
- And this is Mike.
- Mr. Mike.

1166
01:12:32.500 --> 01:12:33.416
[Ganesh] Thank you so much.

1167
01:12:33.500 --> 01:12:35.041
- [body slumps]
- [Vijay] Mike?

1168
01:12:35.125 --> 01:12:40.375
[dramatic music playing]

1169
01:12:46.291 --> 01:12:49.041
[winch clangs. whirrs]

1170
01:12:49.125 --> 01:12:56.083
[foreboding music playing]

1171
01:13:02.750 --> 01:13:03.916
[door opens]

1172
01:13:10.125 --> 01:13:12.208
No lights. They'll be searching for us.

1173
01:13:12.291 --> 01:13:14.708
Vijay. cut the generator
and draw the curtains.

1174
01:13:14.791 --> 01:13:20.666
[foreboding music continues]

1175
01:13:20.750 --> 01:13:23.500
[Mike groaning]

1176
01:13:26.083 --> 01:13:28.708
[groans]

1177
01:13:29.166 --> 01:13:30.708
No. wait. Wait.

1178
01:13:31.541 --> 01:13:33.333
- There's no time.
- [Dhani] Quiet.

1179
01:13:36.000 --> 01:13:41.208
[foreboding music continues]

1180
01:13:46.375 --> 01:13:49.375
There is a first aid kit
under the driver's seat.

1181
01:13:49.458 --> 01:13:50.559
- [Vijay] Driver's seat.
- Yeah.

1182
01:13:50.583 --> 01:13:51.708
Vijay. go. Go.

1183
01:13:54.500 --> 01:13:56.500
Um. I... I have a surgical kit.

1184
01:13:56.958 --> 01:13:57.833
- Get it.
- [Ganesh] Yes.

1185
01:13:57.916 --> 01:14:01.916
[foreboding music continues]

1186
01:14:02.000 --> 01:14:03.083
Here.

1187
01:14:04.333 --> 01:14:06.458
It's good claw. It's for sheep.

1188
01:14:06.541 --> 01:14:08.708
[foreboding music fades]

1189
01:14:11.541 --> 01:14:15.500
[winds blowing]

1190
01:14:24.666 --> 01:14:25.958
[Rudra] No sleep tonight.

1191
01:14:26.708 --> 01:14:30.000
We're going to search every inch of
the Highlands until we find them.

1192
01:14:32.583 --> 01:14:34.750
Everything that's unnecessary. it goes.

1193
01:14:35.500 --> 01:14:37.958
We will make this bus
as light as we can. okay?

1194
01:14:39.250 --> 01:14:40.250
Why. Baba?

1195
01:14:40.500 --> 01:14:42.860
Well. it makes it easier for the crane.
you know. because...

1196
01:14:43.041 --> 01:14:44.041
Oh. I hadn't told you.

1197
01:14:44.583 --> 01:14:45.750
The bridge isn't built yet.

1198
01:14:47.250 --> 01:14:49.583
[Vijay] Wait.
Are we going to crane over the gorge?

1199
01:14:49.666 --> 01:14:52.250
Like we did in the old days.
In a much older crane.

1200
01:14:53.750 --> 01:14:55.166
I wish I'd seen the old days.

1201
01:14:56.166 --> 01:14:59.125
What? You will see the new days.

1202
01:14:59.833 --> 01:15:00.833
See...

1203
01:15:01.000 --> 01:15:02.458
I am old. [Chuckles]

1204
01:15:02.958 --> 01:15:05.041
- I am ready to go.
- Don't say that.

1205
01:15:05.750 --> 01:15:06.750
Baba.

1206
01:15:07.208 --> 01:15:08.625
Grandpa lived almost a century.

1207
01:15:09.208 --> 01:15:10.833
But our grandfather is tough.

1208
01:15:11.916 --> 01:15:14.041
Me? Nah. Not so much.

1209
01:15:15.625 --> 01:15:16.458
[Vijay] You're a hero.

1210
01:15:16.541 --> 01:15:19.291
[somber music playing]

1211
01:15:19.375 --> 01:15:20.666
I am no such thing.

1212
01:15:21.666 --> 01:15:22.666
You know...

1213
01:15:24.208 --> 01:15:26.500
I haven't done
one heroic thing in my life.

1214
01:15:29.375 --> 01:15:30.583
You're a hero to me. Papa.

1215
01:15:33.541 --> 01:15:35.041
[chuckles]

1216
01:15:35.541 --> 01:15:37.416
Oh. my boy. Thank you.

1217
01:15:37.500 --> 01:15:41.916
[somber music continues]

1218
01:15:42.000 --> 01:15:43.166
[speaking Hindi]

1219
01:15:43.250 --> 01:15:45.166
We have a full night's work
ahead of us. see.

1220
01:15:48.875 --> 01:15:50.166
[flesh squelching]

1221
01:15:50.250 --> 01:15:51.875
- [grunts]
- [Mike groans]

1222
01:15:51.958 --> 01:15:56.916
[somber music continues]

1223
01:15:57.000 --> 01:15:58.000
[bullet clatters]

1224
01:16:02.125 --> 01:16:03.708
- [Mike groans]
- [Dhani] Hmm.

1225
01:16:03.791 --> 01:16:10.166
[somber music continues]

1226
01:16:13.083 --> 01:16:15.250
[scraping]

1227
01:16:15.333 --> 01:16:18.833
[pestle grinding]

1228
01:16:22.875 --> 01:16:23.875
Will he live?

1229
01:16:34.500 --> 01:16:38.416
- [mortar thuds]
- Mr. McCann... [speaking Nepali]

1230
01:16:41.250 --> 01:16:42.916
[exhales sharply] Means hard to kill.

1231
01:16:44.166 --> 01:16:45.500
Starr. I need your help.

1232
01:16:46.125 --> 01:16:47.166
Yeah. tell me what to do.

1233
01:16:51.458 --> 01:16:53.625
Go to the lake and refill this.

1234
01:16:53.708 --> 01:16:55.250
- Okay.
- Careful.

1235
01:17:00.833 --> 01:17:01.666
[door closes]

1236
01:17:01.750 --> 01:17:04.208
[crickets chirping]

1237
01:17:13.958 --> 01:17:17.250
[water gurgling]

1238
01:17:17.333 --> 01:17:19.333
[bike engine revving]

1239
01:17:23.291 --> 01:17:25.833
[bike engine revving]

1240
01:17:25.916 --> 01:17:27.750
[ominous music sting]

1241
01:17:28.916 --> 01:17:30.291
[bike engine revving]

1242
01:17:30.375 --> 01:17:32.541
[Ganesh] They're here.
Vijay. move the bus.

1243
01:17:32.625 --> 01:17:34.142
- [Vijay] Okay. Baba.
- [Ganesh] Quickly.

1244
01:17:34.166 --> 01:17:36.458
[bike engine revving]

1245
01:17:37.666 --> 01:17:39.166
[water trickling]

1246
01:17:40.541 --> 01:17:42.583
- [brakes hiss]
- [engine starts]

1247
01:17:42.666 --> 01:17:44.541
[bike engine revving]

1248
01:17:46.250 --> 01:17:51.375
- [bike engine revving]
- [ominous music playing]

1249
01:17:51.458 --> 01:17:55.000
[bike engine idling]

1250
01:17:55.083 --> 01:17:56.083
[bike engine stops]

1251
01:18:01.958 --> 01:18:08.875
[ominous music continues]

1252
01:18:10.458 --> 01:18:13.125
[panting]

1253
01:18:20.875 --> 01:18:22.791
[suspenseful music sting]

1254
01:18:22.875 --> 01:18:26.750
- [Starr whimpers]
- Shh. Shh. Shh. Shh.

1255
01:18:28.916 --> 01:18:29.916
[Starr whimpers]

1256
01:18:30.791 --> 01:18:34.666
- [knife slashes]
- [groans. gurgling]

1257
01:18:37.291 --> 01:18:38.166
[Starr gasps]

1258
01:18:38.250 --> 01:18:40.416
- [knife slices]
- [body thuds]

1259
01:18:40.500 --> 01:18:44.416
[ominous music plays]

1260
01:18:44.500 --> 01:18:45.500
[Starr] Oh. my God.

1261
01:18:46.791 --> 01:18:48.583
[breathing heavily]

1262
01:18:53.208 --> 01:18:54.416
[Dhani] Take his weapons.

1263
01:18:54.500 --> 01:18:55.500
We will need them.

1264
01:18:57.208 --> 01:18:58.208
Go.

1265
01:18:59.375 --> 01:19:00.208
- Vijay.
- Yeah.

1266
01:19:00.291 --> 01:19:01.458
The lake. Take his legs.

1267
01:19:01.541 --> 01:19:03.000
[door opens]

1268
01:19:06.041 --> 01:19:10.000
[Starr breathing heavily]

1269
01:19:10.083 --> 01:19:11.083
[door closes]

1270
01:19:13.750 --> 01:19:19.666
[pensive music playing]

1271
01:19:21.333 --> 01:19:24.250
[breathing heavily]

1272
01:19:25.541 --> 01:19:26.833
We who follow The Way...

1273
01:19:27.625 --> 01:19:29.958
are permitted to defend the innocent.

1274
01:19:31.333 --> 01:19:32.208
I'll teach you.

1275
01:19:32.291 --> 01:19:35.250
[inspirational music playing]

1276
01:19:35.333 --> 01:19:36.333
Come.

1277
01:19:39.291 --> 01:19:41.291
I can't teach you much in one night.

1278
01:19:42.875 --> 01:19:44.125
Will you do your best?

1279
01:19:47.583 --> 01:19:48.583
Yes.

1280
01:19:50.875 --> 01:19:51.875
Absolutely.

1281
01:19:52.458 --> 01:19:53.583
Yes is enough.

1282
01:19:55.875 --> 01:19:59.500
Listen. Our enemies are street fighters.

1283
01:20:00.208 --> 01:20:01.791
Tough without discipline.

1284
01:20:02.500 --> 01:20:03.500
They announce...

1285
01:20:04.250 --> 01:20:05.833
when they are about to strike.

1286
01:20:07.000 --> 01:20:08.125
It's their "tell."

1287
01:20:10.583 --> 01:20:11.583
All right.

1288
01:20:12.208 --> 01:20:13.250
When you see the "tell"...

1289
01:20:14.041 --> 01:20:15.333
you go to this position.

1290
01:20:16.208 --> 01:20:17.208
Block.

1291
01:20:18.125 --> 01:20:19.250
Then strike.

1292
01:20:19.333 --> 01:20:21.250
[inspirational music continues]

1293
01:20:21.333 --> 01:20:22.625
- Block.
- [Dhani] Hmm.

1294
